title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.6: NATIONAL CAPACITIES HAS STRENGHTEN FOR SUSTANABLE ACCESS TO Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH)

description.narrative: Basic water services and sanitation facilities are continuously available for children and their families living in areas at risk of food insecurity., which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Disaster Risk Reduction, Environmental Sustainability, Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2022, newborns, children under-five, adolescents, and pregnant and lactating women, increasingly utilize quality health, nutrition HIV and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services and families adopt healthy and hygienic behaviours and practices, including during emergencies.
